Package: XeniumClean
Title: Spatial Neighbour-Aware Transcript Cleanup for Imaging-Based Spatial Transcriptomics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rachael", "Zemek", , "rachael.zemek@auckland.ac.nz",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Removes biologically implausible transcripts from imaging-based spatial
    transcriptomics data (Xenium, MERSCOPE, CosMx) by combining a single-cell RNA-seq
    reference with spatial neighbourhood information. For every cell, the package
    identifies which neighbouring cells belong to other cell types and erases only those
    transcripts that the reference says cannot plausibly originate from the cell's own
    type. This respects physical adjacency and never removes transcripts a cell could
    genuinely express.
